social_posts.post_text: Checking out some new projects in Hidden Hills today. Look at this view from one of the primary suites 😍
Happy Holidays 🌺

I’ve been happy with my new cut, hair color and skin treatments lately.  Trying to stay 37 forever! Here are a few unfiltered shots I’m bravely posting 😂

Love to you all ♥️

After a few years of allowing my hair to grow naturally with length and color, I finally felt like it was the right time to change to something that highlights me properly. 😉

This change comes with personal, professional change and inner growth. New found strength and a clearer vision of a healthy n happier life. I feel like I’ve shed dead weight and grew into a woman I’m happy with with in life as a mom and my job as a professional real estate agent. 

Hey, sometimes change is a good thing even if it’s small. Let’s keep pushing forward!!

Love ya
Cheers ♥️
Really enjoy learning real estate and all the different style of homes that exist out there in LA. I have a long way to go to become an expert but I take in the good when I can along the way!!

I remember being on the phone with this sweet lady who taught real estate in class.  She told me I had to take a 6 months class and pass the huge CA real estate exam I almost barfed because I barely even have an education so a TEST!?! NOOOOO LOL

“I can’t do this, I have learning problems, I never really focused on school of any kind”

Got the books, opened the first page and read every page of those books. Passed first try. 

3 years later… I’m showing and selling real estate and never in a million years thought would be possible. 

Love ya

Just listed!!!!

Check out my new listing in Los Feliz. I’m so beyond excited to be apart of this special and unique home. 

Listed with @ernie.carswell 
@spencer.daley.re 

Link in bio for more!!

Found a moment during inspections to just appreciate so many things that are happening today. 
To be in escrow is always so exciting. 

I’m so beyond grateful to have a few amazing supportive experts around to learn from and help guide deals while I’m growing and learning. 
From my team around me to the other side…happy escrow! 

🏡
Look at this. Ugh. So grateful to be doing business in Malibu today. ☀️

Change is painfully beautiful.  Sometimes it takes all the strength you have and uncomfortable sacrifices. Staying focused even through the ups and downs and set backs.  I choose to see the beauty. Life is beautiful. ♥️
Brokers open

Looking through old photos, I came across the first home Ernie and I sold together in the Hollywood Hills. 

There were no cameras around. Just me, Ernie and interested buyers of the gorgeous home we were representing.  Put myself together and we sold it with class and love after multiple offers. 

It’s been a journey since this sale and it’s not easy all the time. Truly feel the ups and downs especially with the economy being a single mom. 

I’m so proud of the 2nd season show I finalized filming last year and grateful for it.  Should be airing soon..will keep you all updated.

Season 1 of Kendra Sells Hollywood will be shown again on HGTV this Friday April 21st 9/8c. 

Seems like so long ago in real estate time and it’s a journey. Enjoy!! 

#hgtv #kendrasellshollywood @hgtv

This pic in real estate class was after years not knowing what I was going to do in life to get back on my feet. Before a show was a thought. 

I created space to learn and find purpose again being a single mom. 

Choosing to tv again and to share the journey from the beginning was a fun idea but It hasn’t been easy on and off camera. 

Getting to know all new people and settling into a new world is a process. I will not be the expert over night and have a long way to go after 3 years now but I’m making progress with closed deals and things I’m working on now. 

The show is fun to do but keep in mind that I’m also entertaining too. Keeps things fun and that’s the other job I do. 

Love ya and thanks for watching. ♥️
My real estate journey continues!!!!NEW season of #KendraSellsHollywood premieres May 26 on Max! #StreamOnMax
Just a few pics from last week…touring different homes around LA. Seeing what’s on and off the market. ☀️

Before I start promoting my NEW season of KSH which will start streaming on MAX this Friday the 26th,  I’d like to give a huge thanks to everyone who participated in making this new season a huge hit. 

Without a great production, a few great fellow real estate agents, real real estate clients n friends who supported me in real life, a strong new network, we wouldn’t have been able to create a powerful show.  It was intense, fun, dramatic, emotional and a chapter of a real journey to become the best agent in the world for myself and my kids. 

Definitely not easy though with the past creepin in but still don’t regret a thing and grateful for everything that has helped get me here today. (We touch on that this season) 

Ok back to ironing my dress for tomorrows press day.  Love ya

#KendraSellsHollywood #StreamOnMax

Up close and personal and #theonetowatch 

New season #KendraSellsHollywood 

@streamonmax Friday MAY 26

🏡

I want to thank those who have supported me through the ugly painful times I’ve had to go through to make certain breakthroughs in life. 

I spend more time alone, focused on simple little ways to get better as a mom and business woman and it’s not as glamorous as it used to be.  To find who I am in the real estate world is so important and it’s exciting to have this chance. 

It’s incredible to learn the real life of a real real estate agent and holy crap I respect those that have made it in the business. BRAVO. I look up to you!

These last few days Ive focusing on how to be better agent for my clients. What I can do to help them feel like they are making a smart decision while purchasing a home and today I wake up with a new season of Kendra Sells Hollywood streaming on MAX. Yaaaaa. It’s out!!!! 

@streamonmax #kendrasellshollywood #theonetowatch

Had a great 24 hours in the OC for my bday weekend.  My daughter and I stayed at the @lacasahotellb which was cool because our 3 bedroom suite was steps from the beach and ate of the rooftop. We played 9 holes at @strawberryfarms with friends and to see my daughter go out there and crush it, just made turning 38 that much more special. 

June 12 is my actual bday but today and this new year will be about letting go and accepting life as it is, enjoying time more rather than stressing so much about things I can’t control, moving forward and trusting that I am enough to make each day great for myself and for my kids, surround myself with those who want to smile…time is so precious!! 

I see your messages and I love you guys. Thank you for being apart of my crazy journey!!
